The paper presents a soft robotic hand with embedded sensing and computation for successful grasping. The focus is on the design and control of the robotic hand, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of embedded computation and sensing also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the advantages of soft robotics, which could relate to mechanical engineering (cs.ME). Finally, the paper demonstrates the grasping of objects, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV) for object recognition and tracking.
